profile_positions.description:
As part of the global digital team at Randstad I led the initiative to implement local optimization programs in the 39 Randstad countries. I set the global digital optimization strategy and advised local teams on how to grow their teams, improve subject knowledge and increase the effectiveness of their processes. I've trained CRO professionals and stimulated knowledge exchange and collaboration between the different global teams. I've partnered with different departments and external agencies.

Some of my accomplishments:
✔ Centralized CRO tooling (Optimizely X, Effective Experiments, Hotjar) with global access for all local teams;
✔ Onboarded a global agency that brings us extra development power to run more global experiments;
✔ Changed the CRO process from ad-hoc, low-impact and fragmented to structured, high-impact and much more customer and results driven;
✔ Increased the experiment pace in one year from around 50/year to 500/year;
✔ Brought separated local teams together in a global CRO team (40+ people) that actively shares local knowledge and built experiments together;
✔ Branched out to offline innovation projects to assist with their experimental designs to make sure new ideas can be properly validated.

Some of the tools I used: Optimizely, Effective Experiments, Hotjar, Jira, Google Analytics Premium and Google Data Studio.

I regularly represented Randstad at public workshops and conferences to share my experience.
